    "body": "I don't understand. I've tried this. In my index.html loaded by index.js I've put this :\n\n```\n<script>\n  window.app = require('remote').require('app');\n</script>\n<iframe src=\"http://mywebapp.dev\"></iframe>\n```\n\nIn the goal to get the app object in my webapp via `window.parent.app`. But my app crash with this message : \"Uncaught SecurityError: Blocked a frame with origin \"http://mywebapp.dev\" from accessing a frame with origin \"file://\".  The frame requesting access has a protocol of \"http\", the frame being accessed has a protocol of \"file\". Protocols must match.\".\n\nIt's because I can't access the parent frame because the protocol differsâ€¦ So how can I do?\n"
