    "updated_at": "2015-05-22T14:37:15Z",
    "body": "Oh! I think I've found the solution. I load my webapp directly :\n\n`mainWindow.loadUrl('http://mywebapp.dev');`\n\nthen in the index.html of my webapp, I add this first script :\n\n```\n<script>\n      if (window.require) {\n        window.electionRemote = require('remote');\n        delete window.require;\n        delete window.module;\n      }\n</script>\n```\n\nThen I can access the `electionRemote` object in my angular code.\n"
  },
